        <section name="DataNucleus Spatial">
            <p>
                <i>datanucleus-spatial</i> provides support for persistence of many geometric/spatial datatypes.
                It builds on top of the <i>datanucleus-core</i> persistence capabilities, and is used in conjunction
                with the <i>datanucleus-rdbms</i> plugin.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Compile Requirement : JDK1.5+</li>
                <li>Runtime Requirement : JDK1.5+</li>
                <li>Latest version : 3.2.4</li>
                <li>Roadmap : <a href="http://issues.datanucleus.org/browse/NUCSPATIAL?report=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.project:roadmap-panel" target="_blank">Via JIRA</a></li>
                <li>License : <a href="../project/license.html">Apache 2</a></li>
                <li>Javadocs : <a href="../javadocs/store.types.spatial/3.2">3.2</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.types.spatial/3.1">3.1</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.rdbms.spatial/3.0">3.0</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.rdbms.spatial/2.2">2.2</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.rdbms.spatial/2.1">2.1</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.rdbms.spatial/2.0">2.0</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.rdbms.spatial/1.1">1.1</a>,
                               <a href="../javadocs/store.rdbms.spatial/1.0">1.0</a></li>
                <li>Source : <a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/datanucleus/code/HEAD/tree/platform/store.rdbms.spatial/trunk/">latest</a></li>
            </ul>

